replies.body:
On the one hand, he won't/shouldn't be able to instant-stun people anymore. But he can still zone with it - they see the circle on the ground, they have 3 options: 

- they move away from it and don't get stunned, but now have to move around it or back up (making it good for disengage);
- they don't move and get stunned (either because they don't pay attention or got hit by some other CC);
- or they end up inside the event horizon, leaving them to either blow an escape ability to get out unscathed or to remain inside and with limited space to dodge Veigar's Q and W (and anything else that Veigar's team throws at them).

Fun thought: If Veigar has a Janna on his team, and he uses his E, and those inside the circle don't fall for it, but then Janna gets in the center and uses her ult... wombo combo :P I can see this work with Gragas as well, though in either case skill would be needed.
